    "created_at": "2016-01-27T00:18:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-01-27T00:18:28Z",
    "body": "This kind of discussion, where there isn't a concrete answer, is best on [Discuss, the official Atom (and Electron!) forum](https://discuss.atom.io).\n\nIn general, Electron is a framework that is designed to allow you to use web technologies to build desktop applications. This tends to point towards applications architected like Atom, where the code for the application and all of its packages is installed and executed locally even if data is obtained via network connections. I'm sure there are situations where different trade-offs might well be useful. This is just the main focus of the current design.\n"
